{
  "doc_id": "16467",
  "text": "Work has been also done in predicting demographic characteristics of users based on the pages they visited. For example, in [CITATION_1] authors used the content and categories of the pages visited by the users to predict their gender and age group. They proposed combination of SVM and Latent Semantic Indexing [CITATION_2] to reduce the sparseness in the data. User profiling was also prominent topic in ad targeting community with most of the work focusing on personalizing display ads process to maximize clicks [CITATION_3] [9] [CITATION_4] . In our work we do not directly address ad targeting, even though the proposed modeling of user segments can be exploited in ad targeting. Our approach differs from the related work in combining access logs and page content with semantic information from different data sources. Moreover, we enable user modeling based on characteristics of the targeted user subset, where some data may be missing for some of the users.",
